I"ß<p>Cablegram 28, CANBERRA, 3 February 1949, 9 p.m.</p>

<p>CONFIDENTIAL</p>

<p>KOREA 1. Section of report of Delegation on Korean Question and speech[1] of Australian delegate to first committee are being forwarded by air.</p>

<p>2. We feel that Australian representative should endeavour to concentrate attention of the commission on the attainment of Korean unity by methods described in paragraph 4 (b) of resolution[2] i.e. removal of barriers to economic, social and other friendly intercourse caused by the division of Korea.</p>

<p>3. Please keep in touch with Indian delegate and act in concert when possible.</p>

<p>_[1] Document 158.</p>

<p>[2] See Document 157.</p>

<p>_</p>

<p><em>[AA : A1838, 852/20/4, V]</em></p>
